description: This table presents the quantitative results of time series imputation experiments on three datasets: PM2.5, PhysioNet 0.1, and PhysioNet 0.5. caption: Table 2: Single-sample test imputation results on PM 2.5, PhysioNet 0.1, and PhysioNet 0.5 (5-trial averages).
description: This table presents the results of a single-sample imputation test using the CSDI and CLWF methods on three datasets: PM2.5, PhysioNet 0.1, and PhysioNet 0.5.  The results are averaged across 5 trials and show the Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) and Mean Absolute Error (MAE) for each method and dataset.  This allows for comparison of the methods' performance when only a single sample is used for imputation, highlighting the efficiency and accuracy of CLWF.

caption: Table 3: Test imputation results on PM 2.5 (5-trial averages).
description: This table presents the results of the time series imputation experiment on the PM 2.5 dataset. Two versions of the proposed method, CLWF, are compared: one without Rao-Blackwellization (RB) and one with RB.  The table shows that incorporating RB slightly improves the RMSE and MAE values.  The results demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method and the benefit of incorporating the Rao-Blackwellization technique.
